[With the updated totals for scarlet fever so far this year (2011) of
87 cases in Macau, 1100 cases in Hong Kong, and 847 cases in
Guangdong, the incidence rate of scarlet fever for Macau, with a
population of about 544 000 in 2010
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macau), is 15.9 per 100 000; that for
Hong Kong, with a population of 7 million in 2010
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong), is 15.7 per 100 000; and
that for Guangdong, with an estimated population of 110 million in
2010 (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guangdong), is 0.8 per 100 000.
For comparison, the annual incidence rates of scarlet fever reported
for Hong Kong in the past decade have been 2 to 3 per 100 000
(http://www.gideononline.com/tag/scarlet-fever/).

Genotypic characterization of outbreak isolates by molecular methods,
such as multilocus sequence typing, ribotyping, pulsed-field gel
electrophoresis (PFGE), and random amplified polymorphic DNA (RAPD)
analysis, will aid identifying common outbreak strains. We await this
information.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Hong Kong and neighboring
China and Macau can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/0_xc. -
Mod.ML]
